**1) Analysis of the Main Target Image**

• **Block Count & Layers**  
  – There are a total of 15 blocks.  
  – They form roughly three layers:  
    1. Bottom layer of three red arches (forming a “bench”) plus four orange cylinders (the “legs”).  
    2. Second layer of four green rectangular blocks on top of the red arches, and two yellow rectangular blocks forming a “tabletop” on the orange cylinders.  
    3. Third layer consisting of one tall orange cylinder standing on the tabletop, capped by one yellow half‐cylinder.

• **Spatial Relationships**  
  – Three red arch‐shaped blocks line up side‐by‐side.  
  – Four small green rectangular blocks sit in a row on top of these arches.  
  – Behind the arches are four orange cylinders arranged in a rectangle; the two yellow rectangular blocks sit on top of those cylinders.  
  – A fifth orange cylinder rises from the left side of the tabletop; the yellow half‐cylinder rests on top of that tall cylinder.

---

**2) Selecting Required Blocks From the Dictionary**

Below are the exact matches (no rotation allowed beyond what is shown):

• **Red arches (3 needed):** Block #1  
• **Green rectangular blocks (4 needed):** Block #4  
• **Yellow rectangular “tabletop” blocks (2 needed):** Block #9  
• **Orange vertical cylinders (5 needed):** Block #12  
• **Yellow half‐cylinder “cap” (1 needed):** Block #14  

Hence the block indices required (with repeats) are:  
1, 1, 1, 4, 4, 4, 4, 9, 9, 12, 12, 12, 12, 12, 14
